Module com.gyp1.inventorymgtapp

Package com.gyp1.inventorymgtapp

package com.gyp1.inventorymgtapp
  • Class
    Description
    ConfirmDialog
    The ConfirmDialog class creates a custom confirm dialog using JavaFX's Dialog class.
    InHouse
    The InHouse class is a child of the Part class.
    Inventory
    The Inventory class encapsulates the attributes and behaviors of an inventory object.
    InventoryMgtApp
    The InventoryMgtApp class is the starting point of the app (system).
    MainController
    The MainController controls the main view and provides linkage to the PartController and ProductController.
    MessageDialog
    The MessageDialog displays an Alert dialog without creating a new instance.
    Outsourced
    The Outsourced class is a child of the Part class.
    Part
    The abstract class Part encapsulates the attributes that make up a Product.
    PartController
    The PartController contains the logic for updating the parts list in the inventory object from user input via the part-view.fxml based view, and also updating the same view with data from the model.
    Product
    The Product class represents a real-life product as an object of seven attributes: id, name, price, stock, minimum and maximum inventory levels permitted, and a list of Part objects.
    ProductController
    The ProductController contains the logic for updating the products list in the inventory object from user input via the part-view.fxml based view, and also updating the same view with data from the model.
    UserAction
    An enumerated type for specifying whether a user input action is adding or editing data (during Part or Product input).
